children: Predicting Inhibitors for the protein Cathepsin S
_______________is a protein that has been identified as an important factor in the process of tumor growth and invasion in cancer.
The inhibition of this protein using drugs has been used as an additional treatment in cancer that increases the survival rate of the patient.
Finding alternative and more efficient inhibitors is a time and resource consuming process that can be speeded up using data mining methods.
Data set obtained from CHEMBL database
Inputs: SMILES strings representing chemical compounds
Using a chemoinformatic library we could extract over 100 features representing chemical or structural properties of the compound.
After removing low variance features we got 99 features to use in the model
Outputs: Affinity values from experimental data
Features with different scales- needed Normalization and Standadization
We decided to use 20 PCs for dimensionality reduction
Regression on the CHEMBL data set
In Data mining projects for drug discovery problems is important the feature extraction method .
The application of Data mining methods for drug discovery problems would speed up the development of new drugs.
Perspective: Use this models to find differents strong inhibitors from ZINC15 Database ( ~ 230 million compounds)
